"Intro" = "Intro";
"About" = "About";
"A quick intro to how Rundr fits around your Apple Watch runs." = "A quick intro to how Rundr fits around your Apple Watch runs.";
"Start where it matters" = "Start where it matters";
"Build your Session Plan on iPhone, or load one from a predefined list, then head to Apple Watch when you are ready to run." = "Build your Session Plan on iPhone, or load one from a predefined list, then head to Apple Watch when you are ready to run.";
"Plan with precision" = "Plan with precision";
"Use your Session Plan for precise manual distance, or keep it together with GPS in Dual." = "Use your Session Plan for precise manual distance, or keep it together with GPS in Dual.";
"Mark every lap" = "Mark every lap";
"Each lap should be marked with a button press on Apple Watch, or with the Action Button when your watch supports it. That keeps your workout structure clean and stores the laps in Apple Health." = "Each lap should be marked with a button press on Apple Watch, or with the Action Button when your watch supports it. That keeps your workout structure clean and stores the laps in Apple Health.";
"Rest belongs to the lap flow" = "Rest belongs to the lap flow";
"Rest is tied to a lap, so your workout history stays readable. Rundr can also detect rest automatically, which helps when you want the watch to follow the rhythm of the session with less manual work." = "Rest is tied to a lap, so your workout history stays readable. Rundr can also detect rest automatically, which helps when you want the watch to follow the rhythm of the session with less manual work.";
"Bring good sessions back" = "Bring good sessions back";
"When the run is done, your session is waiting on iPhone for review. Reuse the ones that worked, adjust the ones that did not, and keep moving without rebuilding everything from scratch." = "When the run is done, your session is waiting on iPhone for review. Reuse the ones that worked, adjust the ones that did not, and keep moving without rebuilding everything from scratch.";
"Rundr is built for interval days." = "Rundr is built for interval days.";
"It is a running app designed around Apple Watch first, with iPhone handling the setup and the follow-up. The goal is simple: make structured runs feel easier to start, easier to follow, and easier to return to." = "It is a running app designed around Apple Watch first, with iPhone handling the setup and the follow-up. The goal is simple: make structured runs feel easier to start, easier to follow, and easier to return to.";
"Flexible when your workout is not one-size-fits-all" = "Flexible when your workout is not one-size-fits-all";
"You can build distance intervals, time intervals, pacing goals, rest blocks, and repeat structures that match the way you actually train. If a session works well, save it and bring it back later." = "You can build distance intervals, time intervals, pacing goals, rest blocks, and repeat structures that match the way you actually train. If a session works well, save it and bring it back later.";
"Made to keep momentum" = "Made to keep momentum";
"Rundr keeps planning, running, and reviewing connected. Set things up on iPhone, run from Apple Watch, then come back to your synced history when you want to repeat a favorite session or tune the next one." = "Rundr keeps planning, running, and reviewing connected. Set things up on iPhone, run from Apple Watch, then come back to your synced history when you want to repeat a favorite session or tune the next one.";
"Overview" = "Overview";
"Example" = "Example";
"Tip" = "Tip";
"Session Plan" = "Session Plan";
"Rundr keeps one current Session Plan. Loading a plan from predefined session plans or from a past session in History replaces the one you have now." = "Rundr keeps one current Session Plan. Loading a plan from predefined session plans or from a past session in History replaces the one you have now.";
"Load last week's 6 × 400 m from History, then adjust one rest before your next run." = "Load last week's 6 × 400 m from History, then adjust one rest before your next run.";
"Sharing" = "Sharing";
"Rundr exports plans and past sessions as files from the iPhone share sheet. Use Share Plan in Adjust Interval to send a plan, or Share Session in a past session detail view to send a session." = "Rundr exports plans and past sessions as files from the iPhone share sheet. Use Share Plan in Adjust Interval to send a plan, or Share Session in a past session detail view to send a session.";
"Send" = "Send";
"On iPhone, Apple's share sheet shows the available ways to send the file. Apple documents that AirDrop can send documents to nearby Apple devices, and that AirDrop requires Wi-Fi and Bluetooth to be turned on." = "On iPhone, Apple's share sheet shows the available ways to send the file. Apple documents that AirDrop can send documents to nearby Apple devices, and that AirDrop requires Wi-Fi and Bluetooth to be turned on.";
"Receive" = "Receive";
"Apple documents that you accept AirDrop transfers from the AirDrop notification, and that some received files may be saved in the Files app. In Rundr, you can import a received Rundr file from More > Import File." = "Apple documents that you accept AirDrop transfers from the AirDrop notification, and that some received files may be saved in the Files app. In Rundr, you can import a received Rundr file from More > Import File.";
"If the file is saved in Files instead of opening in Rundr, open Rundr and use More > Import File." = "If the file is saved in Files instead of opening in Rundr, open Rundr and use More > Import File.";
"For AirDrop, Apple says the devices must be within 30 feet (10 meters), both devices need Wi-Fi and Bluetooth turned on, and the receiver must allow Contacts Only or Everyone for 10 Minutes." = "For AirDrop, Apple says the devices must be within 30 feet (10 meters), both devices need Wi-Fi and Bluetooth turned on, and the receiver must allow Contacts Only or Everyone for 10 Minutes.";
"Mark as Rest" = "Mark as Rest";
"Mark as Rest turns the current lap into rest. That rest stays attached to the lap you just finished, so it remains part of the workout." = "Mark as Rest turns the current lap into rest. That rest stays attached to the lap you just finished, so it remains part of the workout.";
"With Timed Rest" = "With Timed Rest";
"Rundr starts rest after the lap and warns in the last 5 seconds if Rest Alerts is enabled in Settings. When passed, the next lap does not start by itself. The target rest is a guide, and you still decide when the next lap begins." = "Rundr starts rest after the lap and warns in the last 5 seconds if Rest Alerts is enabled in Settings. When passed, the next lap does not start by itself. The target rest is a guide, and you still decide when the next lap begins.";
"Use Manual when you want to choose exactly when Mark as Rest starts and ends. Use Auto-detect when you want Rundr to enter rest after you stop and end it again when you move." = "Use Manual when you want to choose exactly when Mark as Rest starts and ends. Use Auto-detect when you want Rundr to enter rest after you stop and end it again when you move.";
"How Auto-detect Works" = "How Auto-detect Works";
"Auto Rest marks the current lap as rest after you stop moving. That rest stays attached to the same lap. Rundr does not create a new lap by itself. The next lap starts when you press lap." = "Auto Rest marks the current lap as rest after you stop moving. That rest stays attached to the same lap. Rundr does not create a new lap by itself. The next lap starts when you press lap.";
"Finish a 400 m rep, stop at the rail, and the current lap becomes rest. When you are ready for the next rep, press lap to start the next lap." = "Finish a 400 m rep, stop at the rail, and the current lap becomes rest. When you are ready for the next rep, press lap to start the next lap.";
"Interval Type" = "Interval Type";
"Use Distance when the lap has a known distance, like 400 m or 1 km." = "Use Distance when the lap has a known distance, like 400 m or 1 km.";
"Use Time when you want to define how long the lap should last, rather than how far it should be." = "Use Time when you want to define how long the lap should last, rather than how far it should be.";
"Choose Time for 45 s with 15 s rest, or name it Jog for an easier segment." = "Choose Time for 45 s with 15 s rest, or name it Jog for an easier segment.";
"Tracking Mode" = "Tracking Mode";
"Manual" = "Manual";
"Manual uses your Session Plan and manual lap presses without GPS distance. Use it for distance intervals when you want full control and precise measurement and statistics." = "Manual uses your Session Plan and manual lap presses without GPS distance. Use it for distance intervals when you want full control and precise measurement and statistics.";
"Dual" = "Dual";
"Dual keeps the Session Plan and also records GPS distance. Use it when you want time-based laps. Time intervals need GPS, so Rundr uses Dual there." = "Dual keeps the Session Plan and also records GPS distance. Use it when you want time-based laps. Time intervals need GPS, so Rundr uses Dual there.";
"Apple Health" = "Apple Health";
"Apple Health lets Rundr save workouts, laps, heart rate, energy, and GPS routes when available, and read the workout data it needs back. Turn it on when you want your runs to stay in Apple's fitness history." = "Apple Health lets Rundr save workouts, laps, heart rate, energy, and GPS routes when available, and read the workout data it needs back. Turn it on when you want your runs to stay in Apple's fitness history.";
"Enable Health access if you want one session to appear in Rundr, Health, and Fitness instead of living only inside the app." = "Enable Health access if you want one session to appear in Rundr, Health, and Fitness instead of living only inside the app.";
"Apple Activity" = "Apple Activity";
"Your laps and workout details can also appear in Apple's Activity and Fitness views because Rundr saves the session as a workout with interval activities. That is useful for sharing, checking the route, or reviewing the workout outside Rundr." = "Your laps and workout details can also appear in Apple's Activity and Fitness views because Rundr saves the session as a workout with interval activities. That is useful for sharing, checking the route, or reviewing the workout outside Rundr.";
"After syncing, you can open the workout in Apple's Activity or Fitness view, share it from there, or import it into other fitness apps that support it." = "After syncing, you can open the workout in Apple's Activity or Fitness view, share it from there, or import it into other fitness apps that support it.";
