/* Legal */
"Privacy Policy" = "Privacy Policy";
"Terms of Use" = "Terms of Use";
"What Rundr Stores" = "What Rundr Stores";
"Rundr can store your session plans, workout history, app settings, and ongoing workout state on your devices. If you allow Apple Health access, Rundr can read and write workout data such as workouts, laps, heart rate, active energy, running distance, body mass used for calorie estimates, and GPS route data when available." = "Rundr can store your session plans, workout history, app settings, and ongoing workout state on your devices. If you allow Apple Health access, Rundr can read and write workout data such as workouts, laps, heart rate, active energy, running distance, body mass used for calorie estimates, and GPS route data when available.";
"How Rundr Uses Data" = "How Rundr Uses Data";
"Rundr uses this data to run structured workouts, show your history, restore unfinished sessions, calculate workout metrics, sync between Apple Watch and iPhone, and save workouts back to Apple Health when you choose to enable that integration." = "Rundr uses this data to run structured workouts, show your history, restore unfinished sessions, calculate workout metrics, sync between Apple Watch and iPhone, and save workouts back to Apple Health when you choose to enable that integration.";
"Storage and Sync" = "Storage and Sync";
"Rundr does not require an account. Based on the current app design, your workout data is stored locally on your devices and transferred between Apple Watch and iPhone using Apple's system frameworks. Rundr does not use third-party advertising or analytics SDKs." = "Rundr does not require an account. Based on the current app design, your workout data is stored locally on your devices and transferred between Apple Watch and iPhone using Apple's system frameworks. Rundr does not use third-party advertising or analytics SDKs.";
"Permissions and Choices" = "Permissions and Choices";
"You can decide whether to grant Health and location access. If you deny permissions, features such as GPS distance, route recording, heart-rate display, calorie estimates, and Apple Health saving may be limited or unavailable. You can change permissions later in Apple's Settings app." = "You can decide whether to grant Health and location access. If you deny permissions, features such as GPS distance, route recording, heart-rate display, calorie estimates, and Apple Health saving may be limited or unavailable. You can change permissions later in Apple's Settings app.";
"Using Rundr" = "Using Rundr";
"Rundr is a fitness and workout planning app for structured running sessions on Apple Watch and iPhone. It is provided for personal use and does not promise specific training results, uninterrupted availability, or error-free data." = "Rundr is a fitness and workout planning app for structured running sessions on Apple Watch and iPhone. It is provided for personal use and does not promise specific training results, uninterrupted availability, or error-free data.";
"Not Medical Advice" = "Not Medical Advice";
"Rundr is not medical advice and is not intended to diagnose, treat, monitor, or prevent illness or injury. Health and workout data can be incomplete, delayed, or inaccurate. Speak with a qualified medical professional before relying on the app for health or training decisions." = "Rundr is not medical advice and is not intended to diagnose, treat, monitor, or prevent illness or injury. Health and workout data can be incomplete, delayed, or inaccurate. Speak with a qualified medical professional before relying on the app for health or training decisions.";
"Train Safely" = "Train Safely";
"You are responsible for using Rundr safely, staying aware of traffic, surfaces, weather, surroundings, and your own condition, and following local laws and rules wherever you train. Stop using the app immediately if you feel pain, dizziness, distress, or that continued exercise may be unsafe." = "You are responsible for using Rundr safely, staying aware of traffic, surfaces, weather, surroundings, and your own condition, and following local laws and rules wherever you train. Stop using the app immediately if you feel pain, dizziness, distress, or that continued exercise may be unsafe.";
"Your Responsibility" = "Your Responsibility";
"You use Rundr at your own risk. To the fullest extent permitted by law, you are responsible for your training choices and for any accident, injury, damage, loss, or other harmful event that happens while using the app." = "You use Rundr at your own risk. To the fullest extent permitted by law, you are responsible for your training choices and for any accident, injury, damage, loss, or other harmful event that happens while using the app.";
"Availability and Updates" = "Availability and Updates";
"Some features depend on Apple Watch, Apple Health, location services, and other Apple systems being available. Features may change over time. If these terms are updated in a future release, continued use of Rundr means you accept the updated terms." = "Some features depend on Apple Watch, Apple Health, location services, and other Apple systems being available. Features may change over time. If these terms are updated in a future release, continued use of Rundr means you accept the updated terms.";
